==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Innocuous
<hw>In*noc"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>innocuus</ets>; <ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>nocuus</ets> hurtful, fr.
<ets>nocere</ets> to hurt. See <er>Innocent</er>.]</ety> <def>Harmless;
producing no ill effect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A patient, <qex>innocuous</qex>, innocent man.</q>
<rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*noc"u*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In*noc"u*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the salt sea <qex>innocuously</qex> breaks.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Innodate</ent>⟦br⟧
